      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 68: The RTT component treats any RTT as congestion (`ewmaRtt_ / congestionRttScale`). With the current defaults, a normal 100 ms RTT contributes 0.10 after weighting, already above the 0.08 congestion threshold even with 0% loss, causing repeated bitrate decreases on healthy long-distance calls. Use an RTT baseline/excess value, or raise the threshold so normal RTT alone does not trigger draining.\n```suggestion\n    float rttComponent \u003d std::max(0.0f, (ewmaRtt_ - cfg_.baselineRttMs) / cfg_.congestionRttScale);\n```",
